definition.value: A macromolecule consisting of (6R)-5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolic acid with an arbitrary number of glutamic acid residues attached as a polypeptide to the single existent one.
An arylalkylamine in which the aryl group is phenyl.
A gluconate that contains a ketonic carbonyl group.
A glucoside in which the anomeric carbon of the glycosidic bond is in an alpha configuration
A glucoside in which the anomeric carbon of the glycosidic bond is in a beta configuration
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of UDP-rhamnose.
A methyl glycoside in which the H of the OH group on C-1 of galactose is replaced by a methyl group.
A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-homoserine substituted at oxygen with a guanidino (carbamimidamido) group. Although structurally related to L-arginine, it is non-proteinogenic.
An organic phosphonate containing a C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2  group (where R = alkyl group).
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic, Nle, betaPhPro and [S(oxaz)L]-NMe2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Tic, Nle, betaPhPro and [S(oxaz)L]-NMe2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Disc, Nle, betaPhPro and [S(oxaz)L]-NMe2 residues coupled in sequence.
A dipeptide comprising tyrosine with a tyrosyl residue attached to the alpha-nitrogen.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Tic and  Nle-NHCH2CH2Ph residues coupled in sequence.
Tyrosyltyrosine in which each tyrosine residue has L-configuration.
A monomethoxyflavone that is the 4'-O-methyl derivative of kaempferol.
A dipeptide comprising tyrosine with a tyrosyl residue attached to the alpha-nitrogen and with each tyrosine residue being substituted at the 3- and 5-positions by iodine.
An organophosphonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyethylphosphonic acid, arising from deprotonation of one of the two phosphonate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A synthetic tetrapeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Tic and Nle-NHCH2CH2Ph residues coupled in sequence.
3,5-Diiodotyrosyl-3,5-diiodotyrosine in which each tyrosine residue has L-configuration.
A synthetic tetrapeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Tic and Nle-NHCH2Ph residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic tetrapeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Tic and Nle-NMeBn residues coupled in sequence.
An alkanesulfonic acid obtained by the formal substitution of one of the methyl hydrogens of (2S)-propane-1,2-diol by a sulfonic acid group.
An organosulfonate oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from the sulfonic acid group of (2R)-3-sulfopropanediol.
A synthetic tetrapeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Disc and Nle-NMeBn residues coupled in sequence.
A tripeptide consisting of three tyrosine residues each of which is substituted at the 3- and 5-positions by iodine.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of 2-(2,4,5,7-tetraiodo-6-oxido-3-oxo-8a,10a-dihydroxanthen-9-yl)benzoic acid.
A carbohydrate acid which is the 2-(6-phosphono-alpha-D-mannoside) of D-glyceric acid.
A polysaccharide derivative composed of a backbone of linear tetrasaccharide derivative repeating units that are joined to each other via beta-(1->6)-linkages.
An L-tyrosine derivative having a 3'-O-{[(6-aminohexyl)oxy](hydroxy)phosphoryl}uridine phosphate attached to the phenolic hydroxy group via a phosphoester linkage.
A polyester polymer composed of repeating 3-hydroxycarboxylic acid units.
Any lipid with a phosphodiester bridge between an inositol residue and the ceramide group which contains two phosphoryl groups and a mannose residue.
A nitrogen-containing fatty acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group of any amino fatty acid.
A fatty acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group of any nitrogen-containing fatty acid.
A  ribonucleoside bisphosphate having uracil as the nucleobase.
A methyl glycoside comprising methyl beta-D-glucoside having an beta-D-galactosyl residue at the 4-position.
A branched trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue at the 2-position and an alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the 3-position.
A decaprenyl diphosphate having (E)-stereochemistry exclusively in the double bonds.
A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue at the 2-position and an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residue at the 3-position.
A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside having O(6)-ethylguanine as the nucleobase.
An imidazopyridine consisting of 4,5,6,7-tetrahydro-1H-imidazo[4,5-c]pyridine having 4-(dimethylamino)-3-methylbenzyl, diphenylacetyl and carboxy and groups at positions 1, 5 and 6 respectively
A poison that interferes with the function of the kidneys.
A hormone antagonist that blocks angiotensin receptors.
A pyrimidine having a 4-hydroxyaminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.
A pyrimidine having a 4-nitrosobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.
A pyridine having a 4-hydroxyaminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.
